I found this photograph depicting the landing at Enchon and the type of ladders.

18:08.460 --> 18:11.100
This probably looks somewhat familiar to you.

18:11.100 --> 18:12.420
Very, very much so.

18:12.420 --> 18:16.260
The guy right up at the top was a lieutenant.

18:16.260 --> 18:24.400
And he was killed five or six yards later because when he was getting his men off the

18:24.400 --> 18:33.060
boat and somebody threw a grenade in this guy, he did not fight down in the south.

18:33.060 --> 18:35.660
This was his first combat.

18:35.660 --> 18:39.980
And he covered that grenade saving the men on each side.

18:39.980 --> 18:41.980
He got the medal of honor.

18:42.700 --> 18:45.700
I wish I could remember his name, but I can't.

18:45.700 --> 18:47.700
Okay, let's move on.

18:47.700 --> 18:54.340
This is a photograph that certainly depicts the cold, the snow, the cold.

18:54.340 --> 18:56.980
Just trying to get some sleep, trying to get some rest, right?

18:56.980 --> 18:59.060
Actually we were on the road.

